Title: DATA-DRIVEN LEADERSHIP: Leading A Team With Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

Author: Riley Stout

# This article explores the strategic use of Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) in modern leadership. It discusses how properly implemented KPIs serve as a powerful framework for aligning business goals, tracking progress, and enabling clear, objective decision-making.
# Whether you're a team lead, executive, or aspiring manager, this piece offers valuable insight into transforming your metrics from passive reports into actionable tools for growth.

